(As a simple guideline, try to stick to more traditional roles **Ex. Teemo Jg**.  Not 100% required, not that i can even stop you.)

My list is more for just champions I like in general rather than anything tactical.

Top:  {{champion:92}} 

I dont really play her or anything but i just really like her character. Broken and trying to find her own way. I also kinda like champions that use autos in between abilities. I also have some respect for her mains, she does take a decent bit of skill to use proficiently. 

Jungle: {{champion:113}} 

Sej is a cold hearted fighter. She is extremely strong fighter and and wont take shit from ANYONE. She&#039;s actually my 3rd highest mastery champ. Thaaaat and she also made it on here cause she has **ONE** of the best skins in the game 

http://img05.deviantart.net/320e/i/2014/324/e/9/poro_rider_sejuani_by_polkadotzombie-d871i5b.png

Mid: {{champion:103}} 

This should come as no surprise, I absolutely LOVE Ahri&#039;s character and lore. She&#039;s one of those champs i try to play solely because i like the character so much. I&#039;m not bad at her, but im not great xD

ADC: {{champion:22}} 

Bit contrary to Sej here, Ashe was actually my first main (sitting at 2nd highest mastery). Since she was one of the first champs i played i  grew rather attached. That being said, i kinda stopped playing her much when i realized i suck at ADC.

Support: {{champion:37}} 

If you didnt see this coming you must be Lee Sin. Sona is my current main and the champion that i have the MOST mastery points with. She has a special place in my heart. She&#039;s the one who really showed me the ropes and intricacies of the game. I knew basics with Ashe, but i learned so much more in depth with Sona. And i kinda feel similar to her sometimes, in the fact that i kinda feel without a voice to speak how i really feel sometimes. I am actually pretty horrible at expressing myself. So in that sense i kinda connect with her.

(Sidenote: after reviewing my list i have basically made myself a Harem....)

